<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
    pop-extended.xml: mod-side population overrides.

    Companion to bestiary/genes-extended.xml. Sits next to the staged
    horsey.dll (staged by bin/inject.rs::stage_bestiary, copied from
    this file at mod build/inject time, same as genes-extended.xml).

    Current scope: double the default-pop spawn count.

    Vanilla "default" pop has its spawn counts set per-spawner inside
    data/horsey.tmx (the Tiled world map). Each spawner object carries
    a `count` int property and a `class` string property. Spawners with
    `class="default"` (or any sub-pop inheriting from default) determine
    how many horses appear at world-load time.

    This file ships the OVERRIDE DECLARATION. The mod-side parser /
    spawner hook (TODO D2.2 + a new D2.3 for count multipliers) reads
    it and multiplies the appropriate counts at runtime.

    Schema:
      <spawn_overrides>
        <pop name="<vanilla-pop-name>" count_multiplier="<f32>" />
        ...
      </spawn_overrides>

    Reading semantics:
      For each spawner the engine creates, if the spawner's `class`
      attribute matches a `<pop>` entry below (or inherits from one),
      multiply the spawner's vanilla `count` by `count_multiplier`
      before the engine consumes it. Round half-up to an integer at
      consumption time.

    Why this file format (and not direct horsey.tmx edits):
    - The vanilla horsey.tmx is shipped binary-ish (XML, but the game
      caches it into data/genes.dat after first parse). Editing it
      requires Tiled or matching the engine's parse expectations.
    - The mod already wraps content via bestiary/*.xml staged alongside
      the DLL. Adding pop-extended.xml keeps the mod self-contained.
    - The same hook can later apply per-spawner overrides (different
      multipliers per map region) by extending the schema.

    Plumbing TODOs (tracked in horsey-mod/docs/todo.md under "Phase
    D2-spawn (default-pop count multiplier)"):
    - [ ] D2.5: extend bin/inject.rs::stage_bestiary to copy this file
          next to horsey.dll along with genes-extended.xml.
    - [ ] D2.6: pop_xml.rs parser at DLL attach -> POP_OVERRIDES.
    - [ ] D2.7: detour the TMX spawner-consume call site inside
          FUN_140076a10 (tmx_map_loader) and multiply `count` by
          POP_OVERRIDES lookup. Wrap under modforge::seh::guard.
-->
<pop_overrides>
    <pop name="default" count_multiplier="2.0" />
</pop_overrides>
